"{\n  \"judgement\": \"The argument revolves around the nature of God and the definition of love, with both sides presenting flawed logic and misinterpretations of biblical texts. The people questioning God's love and morality are more in the right than the one claiming God is perfect and only loving.\",\n  \"steering\": \"It seems like we're all getting a bit carried away with our words. Can we try to focus on the actual texts and ideas being discussed, rather than making personal attacks or assumptions about each other's motivations?\"}"